HEADWORD: Plumous
<hw>Plu"mous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
}</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>plumosus</ets>, fr. <ets>pluma</ets>
feather: cf. F. <ets>plumeux</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Having feathers or plumes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Having hairs, or other parts, arranged along an axis
like a feather; feathery; plumelike; <as>as, a <ex>plumose</ex> leaf;
<ex>plumose</ex> tentacles.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Plumosite</ent>⟦br⟧
